Name: Epic Aett Rune
Description: This rune symbolizes the words from a noble's mouth, the speech of a leader, the silvertongue of a merchant. It grants those who channel it greater charm and influence.
Types: Rune
Rune: While wearing or using an item imbued with this rune, you gain the following feature.SPACESPACESilvered TongueSPACEAs an action, you speak honeyed words of deception and illusion. Choose a creature you that can hear you within 30 feet of you. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become charmed by you until the end of your next turn or until you or your companions do anything harmful to it. When this effect ends, the creature is unaware that it was charmed by you.SPACESPACECommanding SpeechSPACEAs an action, you give a speech to a creature within 60 feet of you that can hear you. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be charmed by you. While charmed by you in this way, the target must take the Hide action on their turn. The creature may repeat this saving throw at the end of each of their turns, ending this effect on a success.SPACESPACEFearsomeSPACEAs a bonus action, you impose your presence upon a creature within 30 feet of you. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw or become Frightened of you for 1 minute. The creature may repeat this saving throw if it takes damage from you or your allies.SPACESPACEEnsnaring VoiceSPACEAs an action, you muster forth your power and let it loose in a single word of runic power. Choose a creature within 60 feet of you that can hear you. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become charmed by you for 8 hours, or until you end this effect. On a successful save, the target is only charmed by you for 1 minute. You can only have one creature under the effects of this rune at a time.  

